{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"560f9402-7e33-4d17-bd4e-da6bc22c1c11","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf it's namespaced (e.g., `MyApp.Tests.ReportExporterTests`), the `~` operator does a \"contains\" match, so the first form works without needing the full namespace.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad61598e-f53c-4104-86f1-a2efe53f17ff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly without needing to explore the codebase.\n\nLet me glance at the test file to confirm the class name, but the answer is simple: use the `--filter` option.","outputTokens":198,"requestId":"67D0:39ECA:2C38335:30CBCDF:69FD3CEF"},"id":"ddf3fdb5-5021-463a-b286-6afb449b2959","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:31:33.402Z","parentId":"be858829-3e5f-4eef-aa09-725f6200fc5a"}
